---
title: Full Election Lifecycle — Sequence Diagram
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Admin
    participant SC as Smart Contract
    participant SE as Sync Engine
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant V as Voters / Candidates

    Note over A,V: PHASE 0→1: Setup → Registration
    A->>SC: Deploy, set 3 Merkle roots
    A->>SC: startRegistration(regEnd)
    SC-->>SE: PhaseChanged

    loop Candidates register
        V->>SC: registerCandidate(guid, name, year, gender, pos, proof)
        SE->>SC: Poll CandidateRegistered
        SE->>DB: UPSERT candidates
    end

    Note over A,V: PHASE 1→2: Voting Opens
    A->>SC: startVoting(voteEnd)
    SE->>SC: rebuildMerkleTrees()

    loop Voters cast ballots
        V->>SC: castVote(presId, secId, gmIds, proof)
        SC->>SC: Verify proof + female GM quota
        SE->>SC: Poll VoteCast
        SE->>DB: UPDATE vote_count
    end

    Note over A,V: PHASE 2→3: Election Ends
    A->>SC: endElection()
    SE->>DB: snapshotResults()
    SE-->>A: PhaseChanged(Ended)

    Note over A,V: PHASE 3→0: New Election
    A->>SC: startNewElection()
    SC->>SC: _findWinner(President)
    SC->>SC: _findWinner(Secretary)
    SC->>SC: _selectGMWinners() (2 female + 3 any)
    SC->>SC: Store result, reset to Phase 0
    SE->>DB: snapshot + DELETE candidates
